When an aircraft takes off or lands on a contaminated runway and depending on the amount of water, the water spray may enter the engine and affect its behaviour.

node.text:
Welcome to the first episode of our #TechTuesday series, a guide to show you some of the key moments of a #FlightTest campaign.

Why are flight tests necessary?

Flight testing is performed to ensure the aircraft complies with certification and safety requirements, and meets operational needs. During the flight test campaign we perform specific certification demonstrations, assess general handling qualities, engines and operational performances, in many specific conditions (cold weather, high altitude airports,...). 
We also check aircraft noise emission and systems operations in real life.

Buckle up and sit back, as you’re in for a ride! ✈️ #airbus #airbuslovers #avgeek #aviationgeek #aviationlovers #instaaviation #plane #instaplane #aerospace #pilot #pilotlife #flighttesting

Before a brand new aircraft is delivered to an airline, its various systems and engines need to be checked during an acceptance flight.

Join our #FlightTest team in this video and get your checklist ready! ✈️ #airbus #airbuslovers #avgeek #aviationgeek #aviationlovers #instaaviation #plane #instaplane #aerospace #pilot #pilotlife #flighttesting

VMU for Velocity Minimum Unstick. This is the absolute minimum speed at which an aircraft can take off and is achieved by pitching the aircraft up to the maximum during the take-off roll.
Wondering what it's like to perform a VMU test? Watch this #TechTuesday episode! ✈️ #airbus #airbuslovers #avgeek #aviationgeek #aviationlovers #instaaviation #plane #instaplane #aerospace #pilot #pilotlife #flighttesting 
📸 H. Goussé
